.TH man 1 "21 Jun 2012" "1.0" "rehc man page"
.SH NAME
rehc \- command line tools for rehc
.SH SYNOPSIS
rehc [OPTION]... [ARGS]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Provide command line tools to check status of clustered hosts.
.SH OPTIONS
Options for rehc command are:

        start           Starts REHC application as daemon

        stop <PID>      Stops REHC application, needs the pid of rhec as argument

        console         Start console (erlang), be careful at this point!

        load-avg <IP>   Calculate the percent used of cpu, memory total and
                        memory free for a single host in the cluster, needs the
                        host's ip as argument

        show-apps       Show applications and status of them

        cluster         Show host short names and ip's of cluster members

        help            View this page
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Jorge Garrido (jorge.garrido@morelosoft.com)

